cise provider discovery internals rather than real marshal/unmarshal behavior, use test-local JAXBContextFactory stubs and META-INF/services or JAXBContext.JAXB_CONTEXT_FACTORY properties, and avoid SecurityManager-based package-access tests on newer JDKs where SecurityManager behavior is terminally deprecated/fragile.\",\"risks\":[\"There is no matching org.glassfish.jaxb:jaxb-runtime:4.1.0-M1 release visible; 4.0.9 is the latest RI release and should be verified locally with Gradle/Native Image.\",\"Adding the RI may exercise org.glassfish.jaxb runtime code and its native-image needs, so keep assertions focused on jakarta.xml.bind API behavior and rely on local verification as authoritative.\"]}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_09890b58f82f16cc016a3eb9d71910819691cfae067182102e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 575, "output": 593, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30864, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782495693703, "responseId": "resp_09890b58f82f16cc016a3eb9ce26a881969e2e974020edba4f"}}
